💻 Getting Started <a name="getting-started"></a>
To get a local copy up and running, follow these simple steps.

Prerequisites <a name="prerequisites"></a>
Web server with PHP support (e.g., XAMPP, WAMP)
Web browser
Setup <a name="setup"></a>
Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/AMANUELBRS/clinic-management-system.git
Navigate to the project directory:

cd clinic-management-system
Move the project files to your web server's root directory (e.g., htdocs for XAMPP).
Install <a name="install"></a>
No additional installation is required for the client side. Ensure your PHP environment is properly set up.

Usage <a name="usage"></a>
Start your web server (e.g., XAMPP, WAMP).
Open your web browser and navigate to http://localhost/clinic-management-system.
Run tests <a name="run-tests"></a>
To test the application, open the browser and manually test the user functionalities:

Register as a patient and book an appointment.
Log in as an admin to add a doctor and manage patients.
Log in as a doctor to accept bookings and add reports.
Deployment <a name="deployment"></a>
To deploy the project, follow these steps:

Ensure all environment variables are correctly set.
Use a hosting service that supports PHP, such as Heroku, AWS, or a traditional web hosting provider.
Upload your project files to the hosting server and configure the database connection.
